    "citation": "Sanchez-Alcaraz 1998 9756109",
    "population": "N:62 Sex: - Age: 8 month- 6 yrs WT: -",
    "model_type": "PK",
    "objective": "“To evaluate PPK and the relationship between plasma concentration and DDPVA in a homogeneous group of children with epilepsy”",
    "covariates": "Tested: Age Included: Age",
    "observations": "Model limited to estimate VPA CL in children of 8-72 months. The model describes an asymptotic relation of increased CL as age increases. A linear correlation is found between VPA plasma level and dose administered. Results show show that dose required to reach mean plasma [VPA] decreases with age. A level:dose ratio should be used with care as the inter-individual variation in children <2 yrs is 50%.",
    "dose": "Steady state, oral doses in patients",
    "structure": "Simplified PK model",
    "equations": "if(AGE<24) CL = (((theta1/1000)*WT )*((AGE/12)**theta2))*exp(eta1) if(AGE>24 & AGE<48) CL = (((theta1/1000)*WT )*((AGE/12)**theta2))*exp(eta2) if(AGE>48) CL = (((theta1/1000)*WT )*((AGE/12)**theta2))*exp(eta3) Cipred=DOSE/(CL*Tau) Cobs=Cipred #no error model reported DOSE is VPA dose in mg Tau is dosing interval in hours AGE: in months CL is converted from mL/kg/h to L/h by dividing by 1000*WT",
    "parameter_values": "theta1=47.6 theta2= 0.29 omega1=0.2561 omega2=0.0939 omega3=0.0558",
    "validation": "No / No"
